This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump during a visit to the White House by the Clemson Tigers, the College Football Playoff National Champions. The President praised the team for their hard-fought victory and their determination to never give up. He commended Coach Dabo Swinney for his leadership and noted that the team's success was the result of a vision that began nine years ago. The President also highlighted the individual achievements of some players and expressed his admiration for their skill and resilience. He concluded by congratulating the Clemson Tigers and expressing his hopes for their future success.